# {VAULT_NAME} — second-brain personal vault

> This block is the second-brain vault context. It can stand alone in this directory, or be merged into a parent CLAUDE.md by copy-pasting the section below.

This vault has a `self/` directory (identity, goals, values). The model reads it on session start to keep tone and frame consistent.

## On every session start

1. Read `self/identity.md` and `self/goals.md` to recover voice and threads.
2. Read `vault.md` for the atom contract and verb specs.
3. Glance at `inbox/` and `notes/` (last ~10 by mtime).
4. Surface a one-line orientation: "Hi. Active threads: X. Last memory captured: Y. Anything to add?"

## What this directory is

A personal second-brain — memories, journals, identity. Verbs: `/extract`, `/connect`, `/walk`, `/audit`, `/learn`, `/anneal`, `/init`, `/dream`. Surrender system available but opt-in via `surrender.enabled` in `vault.yaml` (default off; axes are research-shaped, adapt locally if used). Full contract in `vault.md`.
